&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;We are Kao&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;, listed as one of the world’s most ethical companies for the last 19 years.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our brand portfolio spans across three sectors;&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Consumer Care&lt;/strong&gt; (&lt;em&gt;&lt;u&gt;John Frieda, Bondi Sands, Bioré, Jergens, Curél&lt;/u&gt;),&lt;/em&gt;&lt;strong&gt; Professional Hair&lt;/strong&gt; (&lt;em&gt;&lt;u&gt;Goldwell, Oribe, KMS Hair, Kerasilk&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/em&gt;), and &lt;strong&gt;Molton Brown.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our corporate philosophy, the Kao Way, guides us in everything we do – acting with integrity, courageously driving innovation, and treating each other with trust and respect&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Role:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The SAP ERP Application Architect position is responsible for designing and overseeing the implementation of SAP ERP (and related) systems at Kao.&amp;nbsp; They work closely with business analysts, project managers, and other stakeholders to identify business needs and requirements and develop an SAP architecture that meets those needs.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;At Kao, we offer amazing benefits that are available to you on your first day of employment (healthcare, 401(k) plus company match, etc.), 36 total days off (vacation + holidays + sick) and a reasonable salary range of $110,000 - $140,000. &amp;nbsp;We also offer a hybrid work schedule.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you will do:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Review project and design documents for any new implementation/project&amp;nbsp;and enforce EIS standards and guidelines (config and development) &amp;nbsp;to make sure the documentation captures all the business requirements and are uploaded in the appropriate location / site. &amp;nbsp;Will need to guide numerous App Dev team members.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist project teams with the technical design and architecture for new projects and ensure&amp;nbsp;that platforms and technology used adheres to EIS supported standards. &amp;nbsp;Ensure our SAP landscapes and ecosystem is supportable today, tomorrow, and into the future. &amp;nbsp;Architect should be thinking 3-5 years down the road and help ensure we arrive in an intentional place.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work with Business Relationship Managers to understand business requirements and needs and scope out projects with resource requirements and realistic timelines and budgets.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with organizing all existing functional and technical specs and maintaining an inventory&amp;nbsp;of all technical objects and enhancements in our current SAP system to get ready for S/4HANA. Other day-to-day tasks/duties as needed.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Review and research best practices and new technologies and work with the business users&amp;nbsp;to educate and empower them, and implement best in class solutions to keep Kao on the cutting edge of technology.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you will need:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A bachelor&#39;s degree in computer science, information systems, or a related field.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;5+ years’ experience designing and configuring in an SAP environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Minimum 3 full lifecycle implementations / roll outs &amp;amp; support experience in SAP ECC and/or S4 projects.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Business process/functional knowledge and configuration experience in SAP for a set of modules – FICO (financial accounting, asset accounting, overhead accounting, product costing, profitability analysis, financial planning, consolidation, central finance, closing cockpit), Logistics, Materials Management, Sales &amp;amp; Distribution, Warehouse &amp;amp; Quality Management, Production Planning, Plant Maintenance and PLM.&lt;/li&gt;
