&lt;p class=&quot;isSelectedEnd&quot;&gt;This is a key role supporting the FP&amp;amp;A Director for the Professional Haircare business, contributing to global management reporting, business planning, and commercial insight, with a focus on driving financial performance.&amp;nbsp;The FP&amp;amp;A Analyst will support the preparation of annual budgets and forecasts for the salon business, ensuring accuracy, timeliness, and robust planning processes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;isSelectedEnd&quot;&gt;The role involves working closely with stakeholders across R&amp;amp;D, Marketing, functional cost owners, and central FP&amp;amp;A teams. This position goes beyond traditional financial control, providing proactive guidance and support to budget holders on all aspects of budget management and profitability.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you will do:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive the budget &amp;amp; planning process&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Produce management reports and provide clear explanations for performance variances to support organizational objectives. Analyse variances and explore variances/potential problems with line managers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support month-end close activities; ensure timely and accurate reporting.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work with budget holders to ensure they understand the financial information and their impact on organization. Develop and maintain good relationships with all stakeholders. Provide all budget holders with up-to-date information in relation to their budgets.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and implement solutions to improve efficiency on reporting and processes. Attend and contribute to steering/focus groups; support finance projects (global and local) and ad hoc process improvements. Be open to change and adapt to new ways of delivering business services.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you will need:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;isSelectedEnd&quot;&gt;Fully qualified (ACCA, CIMA or equivalent) with a degree in an analytical discipline preferred.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;isSelectedEnd&quot;&gt;4+ years’ experience in relevant finance roles within an international, matrix organisation, with first-hand experience in management accounting, planning, budgeting, and forecasting.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;isSelectedEnd&quot;&gt;FMCG experience is preferred, ideally within a branded, product-led, and consumer- or customer-insight-driven environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li class=&quot;isSelectedEnd&quot;&gt;Advanced financial analysis and business partnering capabilities, with high proficiency in E

